I.r <- vector()  # Create an empty vector

for (i in 1:n){
  # Randomly shuffle income values
  x <- sample(sdf$residual_ols, replace=FALSE)
  # Compute new set of lagged values
  x.lag <- lag.listw(lw, x)
  # Compute the regression slope
  M.r <- lm(x.lag ~ x)
  I.r[i] <- coef(M.r)[2]
}
